      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at the audit from the Rotterdam DC for the Q3 electronic component stock. We've got some weird discrepancies between our WMS and the physical count. Can you look at this table and tell me if you see any patterns or possible reasons for the shrinkage?\n\n| SKU | Description | System Count | Physical Count | Variance |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| CAP-992-X | 10uF Ceramic Capacitor | 14,205 | 14,192 | -13 |\n| RES-441-B | 1k Ohm Resistor (SMD) | 88,400 | 88,385 | -15 |\n| IND-002-K | 10mH Inductor | 2,150 | 2,144 | -6 |\n| DIO-773-L | Zener Diode 5.1V | 5,600 | 5,591 | -9 |\n| TRANS-12-J | NPN Transistor | 3,420 | 3,412 | -8 |\n\nThe numbers are small but it's happening across different categories. Any ideas what's going on?",
